Installation instructions for Lua dissectors

- Launch Wireshark
- In the menu bar, click Help -> About Wireshark
- When the new window pops up, click folders
- Find where it says 'Personal Lua Plugins' and copy the path it shows under Location
- Copy both the zdp dissector and the link layer header dissector into that folder
- In the Wireshark menu bar again, click Edit -> Preferences
- In the preferences window, expand the Protocols section
- Scroll until you find DLT_USER
- Edit the Encapsulations Table
- Click the plus button to add a new user
- Set the Payload protocol to zdp, the Header size to 1, adn the Header protocol to zdp_link_p2p
- Set the trailer size to 0 and leave the Trailer protocol blank
- Click OK to add the User 0 profile, and you're done. 